      <figcaption class="cap"><span class="lead"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16"><use href="#pg-pin"></use></svg> Pattaya's licensed aesthetic clinics span hospital-grade centres to specialist skin clinics</span><span class="credit">Go To Pattaya</span></figcaption></figure>
<!-- TL;DR -->
<div class="tldr">
<h4><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-20"><use href="#pg-info"></use></svg> If you only have 30 seconds</h4>
<p><b>The honest take:</b> Pattaya has good, licensed <b>aesthetic clinics</b> — from hospital-affiliated centres to established skin-clinic chains — but quality varies wildly. <b>Indicative prices:</b> Botox <b>฿8,000–15,000</b> per area, HA dermal filler <b>฿12,000–25,000</b> per syringe, laser hair removal <b>฿1,500–3,000</b> a session, pigmentation (Pico/IPL) <b>฿2,500–6,000</b>, HIFU <b>฿15,000–40,000</b>. The single most important thing is <b>not the price</b> — it's checking the clinic is <b>MoPH/FDA-licensed</b>, that a <b>real doctor</b> injects, and that you see <b>sealed, branded product</b>. This is general information, not medical advice.</p>
</div>
</div>
<!-- LAYOUT -->
<div class="art-layout">
<article class="art-body">
