</div>
<p>Pattaya has quietly become a place people fly in for affordable cosmetic work, and the choice of <strong>aesthetic clinic in Pattaya</strong> ranges from hospital-grade centres to small specialist skin studios on Second Road. The good news is that genuinely excellent, licensed care exists here. The catch is that the same streets also hide "beauty salons" offering cut-price injectables that no responsible doctor would touch. This guide walks through what's on offer, honest indicative prices for 2026, and — the part that actually matters — how to tell a safe, licensed clinic from a risky one. Treat everything below as general information, not medical advice.</p>
<h2 id="treatments">What's available in Pattaya</h2>
<figure class="art-img">
<img alt="Aesthetic clinics pattaya 2 in Pattaya, Thailand" height="428" loading="lazy" src="../Pattaya-Tum-Gorseller-Resized/aesthetic-clinics-pattaya-2.webp" width="760"/>
<figcaption>Aesthetic Clinics Pattaya 2 · Aesthetic Clinics in Pattaya: Treatments, Prices and How to ChooseSafely</figcaption>
</figure>

<p>The menu at a typical <strong>cosmetic clinic in Pattaya</strong> mirrors what you'd find in Bangkok or back home, usually at a lower price. The most requested category is <strong>injectables</strong>: botulinum toxin (Botox and equivalents) to soften frown lines, crow's feet and forehead creases, and hyaluronic-acid (HA) <strong>dermal fillers</strong> for lips, cheeks, chin, jawline and under-eye hollows. These are quick, but they are medical procedures — they belong in the hands of a doctor, not a salon technician.</p>
<p>Beyond needles, <strong>laser treatment in Pattaya</strong> is a big draw: laser hair removal, pigmentation and sun-damage correction (Pico lasers and IPL), and skin resurfacing for texture and acne scars. Energy-based <strong>skin tightening</strong> — HIFU (high-intensity focused ultrasound) and RF (radiofrequency) — is popular for a non-surgical lift along the jaw and neck. Rounding it out are facials, chemical peels, microneedling, thread lifts and bio-remodelling injectables like Profhilo. A good <strong>skin clinic in Pattaya</strong> will steer you toward the smallest effective intervention, not the biggest sale.</p>
<div class="cat-grid">
<div class="cat-card">
<div class="ic"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-24"><use href="#pg-first-aid"></use></svg></div>
<div><div class="label">Injectables</div><b>Botox &amp; fillers</b><p><strong>Doctor-only.</strong> Toxin for lines, HA filler for volume. Effects are temporary and reversible-ish.</p></div>
</div>
<div class="cat-card">
<div class="ic"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-24"><use href="#pg-sun"></use></svg></div>
<div><div class="label">Laser &amp; light</div><b>Hair, pigment, resurfacing</b><p><strong>Pico / IPL.</strong> Needs the right device and settings for Asian and sun-exposed skin.</p></div>
</div>
<div class="cat-card">
<div class="ic"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-24"><use href="#pg-heart"></use></svg></div>
<div><div class="label">Tightening</div><b>HIFU &amp; RF</b><p><strong>Non-surgical lift.</strong> Gradual results over weeks; one of the pricier treatments.</p></div>
</div>
