o a price with a tout who approaches you inside the terminal — that's where the worst airport rip-offs happen."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Is Grab cheaper than a private transfer to Pattaya?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Usually slightly more expensive but more flexible. A Grab from Suvarnabhumi to Pattaya is typically ฿1,500–2,500 with the price shown up front in the app, versus ฿1,300–1,800 for a pre-booked transfer. Grab is the better choice if you don't want to pre-pay or your plans are uncertain; a fixed transfer is better value and removes any surge risk if you book ahead."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Which airport should I fly into for Pattaya?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "If U-Tapao–Pattaya International (UTP) has a convenient flight, it's the easiest — only 40 km and 40 minutes from the city. Most international visitors land at Suvarnabhumi (BKK), about 120 km and two hours away with the most transport options. Don Muang (DMK) also works but is slightly further out at around 150 km and 2 to 2.5 hours."}}]}]$b$);
