</header>
<!-- HERO -->
<figure class="art-hero"><img alt="Areas to be careful pattaya 1 – Areas tobe carefulabout in Pattaya" fetchpriority="high" height="506" loading="eager" src="../Pattaya-Tum-Gorseller-Resized/areas-to-be-careful-pattaya-1.webp" width="1100"/>
      <figcaption class="cap"><span class="lead"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16"><use href="#pg-pin"></use></svg> From Walking Street to Soi 6 · the Pattaya areas to be careful in, mapped honestly by a local</span><span class="credit">Go To Pattaya</span></figcaption></figure>
<!-- TL;DR -->
<div class="tldr">
<h4><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-20"><use href="#pg-info"></use></svg> If you only have 30 seconds</h4>
<p>Pattaya is <b>not a dangerous city</b> — violent crime against tourists is rare — but a handful of zones earn extra caution after dark. Be most alert around <b>Walking Street, Soi 6 and the LK Metro bar sois</b> at 1–4am (bar-bill, drink-spiking and pickpocket risk), on <b>Beach Road and Second Road late at night</b> (motorbike bag-snatchers and timeshare touts), and around <b>Bali Hai Pier and the dark stretch of Beach Road south of Soi 13</b>. The genuinely <b>quiet, low-risk bases</b> are <b>Jomtien, Pratumnak Hill, Naklua and Wong Amat</b>. The single biggest danger here isn't crime at all — it's <b>traffic and rented scooters</b>. Stay sober-ish, watch your bag, agree prices first, and you'll have zero problems.</p>
</div>
</div>
<!-- LAYOUT -->
<div class="art-layout">
<article class="art-body">
<!-- MOBILE STICKY TOC -->
<div class="mtoc">
