ir restaurants over the water serving the area's best-value fresh catch — whole grilled fish from ฿250, prawns by the kilo, a feast for two around ฿700–1,200."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "The fishing pier", "description": "The working heart of town where day-boats land their catch and dive and snorkel trips depart. Best at sunrise and golden hour."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Diving &amp; boat trips", "description": "A main launch point for diving off Pattaya — reef and wreck day trips from ฿2,500–3,500, quieter and cheaper than booking from the city."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 5, "name": "Nearby attractions", "description": "Khao Chi Chan (Buddha Mountain), Silverlake Vineyard, Bang Saray Reservoir and Nong Nooch Tropical Garden are all within 10–15 minutes."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 6, "name": "Quiet stays", "description": "Beachfront resorts (฿1,500–4,000/night), boutique guesthouses (from ฿900) and great-value monthly condos (฿12,000–25,000) for couples, families and long-stayers."}]}, {"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [{"@type": "Question", "name": "Is Bang Saray worth visiting?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, if you want a quiet beach and great-value seafood rather than nightlife and crowds. Bang Saray is a calm fishing town 25 km south of Pattaya with a clean 3 km beach, fresh seafood off the boats (a feast for two runs ฿700–1,200), and nearby sights like Khao Chi Chan and Nong Nooch. It's perfect for a relaxed day trip or a peaceful stay, but skip it if nightlife and malls are your priority."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "How do I get to Bang Saray from Pattaya?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "The easiest way is Grab or Bolt — about ฿300–500 and 30–40 minutes door to door from central Pattaya. A songthaew (baht bus) is cheaper at ฿30–60 but slower and may need a change toward Sattahip. Renting a scooter (฿200–300/day) is 