<h2 id="cave">1. Cave Beach Club — best all-rounder</h2>
<figure class="art-img">
<img alt="Beach clubs pattaya 3 in Pattaya, Thailand" height="428" loading="lazy" src="../Pattaya-Tum-Gorseller-Resized/beach-clubs-pattaya-3.webp" width="760"/>
<figcaption>Beach Clubs Pattaya 3 – explore Pattaya's best spots</figcaption>
</figure>

<p>If you do one beach club in Pattaya, make it <strong>Cave Beach Club</strong> on the south side of <strong>Pratumnak Hill</strong>. It has the rare combination that makes a beach club worth the trip: a genuine stretch of soft sand, a pool set into the rocks with an open sea view, and a kitchen and bar that don't feel like an afterthought. There's <strong>no hard entry fee</strong> — you just spend on food and drink, and a day bed runs from about ฿1,000–1,500 on weekends.</p>
<p>It does daytime lazy and sunset party equally well. From late morning it's loungers, smoothies and a swim; from around 4pm the DJ warms up and the crowd shifts younger and louder. Cocktails are ฿280–380, a wood-fired pizza or burger ฿300–450. The catch: weekends fill up, so arrive before noon or reserve a bed. It's roughly a ฿80–120 Grab from Central Pattaya.</p>
<h2 id="glass-house">2. The Glass House — best for families</h2>
<p>On the quieter <strong>Jomtien</strong> end, <strong>The Glass House</strong> is the one I send families and anyone who wants a calm pool day over a party. The pool is generous and shallow at one end, there's real shade, and the all-day kitchen does food kids will actually eat. The vibe stays mellow even at sunset, so it's a relief if loud DJs aren't your thing.</p>
<p>Expect a <strong>minimum spend of about ฿300–500 per person</strong> rather than a ticket, which a lunch and a couple of drinks clears easily. Sun loungers are usually free with that spend; a cabana is ฿800–1,200. It's a short ฿60–100 ride from Jomtien Beach Road and pairs well with a morning at the beach itself — see our <a class="inline" href="blog-best-beaches-pattaya.html">best beaches near Go To Pattaya</a>.</p>
<h2 id="lima">3. Lima Beach Club — best party</h2>
<p><strong>Lima Beach Club</strong>, also on Pratumnak, is where the beach-club scene goes loudest. Weekend afternoons here are a full party — resident and guest DJs, a packed pool, bottle service and a crowd dressed to be seen. If you want the high-energy, sunset-into-night beach-club experience that fills travel reels, this is the one.</p>
<p>It's the priciest of the regular clubs: a <strong>minimum spend around ฿500–800</strong>, day beds ฿1,500–2,500 at weekends, and a table with bottle service well into the thousands. Cocktails are ฿300–400. Weekday afternoons are far calmer and cheaper if you want the setting without the crush. Note it skews 20s–30s and turns properly adult after dark.</p>
<div class="callout tip">
<div class="ic"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-20"><use href="#pg-info"></use></svg></div>
<div><h4>Local tip</h4><p>"Minimum spend" is your friend, not a trap. At most Pattaya beach clubs there's no ticket — you commit to spending a set amount on food and drink, and you'd spend that on lunch and two drinks anyway. The real money pit is the day bed and bottle service. If you just want a lounger, a swim and a cocktail, you can have a great day for ฿400–600 a head.</p></div>
</div>
<h2 id="others">4–8. The rest of the best</h2>
<p>Five more that round out a proper beach-club week, each with a clear reason to go.</p>
<div class="cat-grid">
<div class="cat-card"><div class="ic"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon"><use href="#pg-wellness"></use></svg></div><span>4. Rabbit Resort Beach</span><b>Quiet &amp; leafy</b><p>Jomtien. A garden-resort beach club for couples who want calm — shaded loungers, a clean pool, no thumping DJ. Free with food and drink; mains ฿250–450.</p></div>
<div class="cat-card"><div class="ic"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon"><use href="#pg-sunset"></use></svg></div><span>5. Bali Hai / Sands</span><b>Best sundowner</b><p>South Pattaya near the pier. Less pool, more view and cocktails as the sun drops over Koh Larn. Min spend ฿400–700; arrive by 5pm for the light.</p></div>
<div class="cat-card"><div class="ic"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon"><use href="#pg-water-sports"></use></svg></div><span>6. Tahiti Beach Club</span><b>Watersports add-on</b><p>Jomtien. A loungers-plus-jet-ski set-up — pair a beach bed with paddleboards or banana boats. Free with F&amp;B; activities priced separately.</p></div>
<div class="cat-card"><div class="ic"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon"><use href="#pg-sea-view"></use></svg></div><span>7. Wong Amat lounges</span><b>Calm north end</b><p>Naklua's <a class="inline" href="blog-best-beaches-pattaya.html">Wong Amat</a> beach. Hotel beach lounges and casual bars on the cleanest sand in town. Low-key, free with a drink, great for a slow day.</p></div>
<div class="cat-card"><div class="ic"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon"><use href="#pg-islands"></use></svg></div><span>8. Koh Larn day clubs</span><b>Best water</b><p>A 45-min ferry away. Tawaen and Samae beaches have the clearest water near Pattaya. Day beds ฿200–400, but it's a full day-trip, not a quick stop.</p></div>
</div>
<p>A note on what to avoid: anything on the main <strong>Beach Road</strong> strip billing itself as a "beach club" is usually just chairs and umbrellas on busy public sand — fine for an hour, not a day. And skip the loudest party clubs on a weekday if you've brought kids; the family-friendly daytime window mostly closes by mid-afternoon.</p>
<h2 id="costs">What a beach club day actually costs</h2>
<p>The number that surprises people is how little a good day costs if you skip the day bed. Here's the realistic 2026 spend per person, in baht. The min-spend almost always counts toward your food and drinks, so you're rarely paying "extra" to be there.</p>
<div class="money-grid">
<div class="money-card"><div class="label">Entry / min spend</div><div class="val">฿0–800</div><p>Most clubs have no ticket; you spend ฿300–800 on F&amp;B instead. Lima and party clubs sit at the top.</p></div>
<div class="money-card"><div class="label">Cocktail</div><div class="val">฿250–400</div><p>Beers ฿120–180. A mocktail or smoothie ฿120–200. Cheaper than a rooftop, dearer than a street bar.</p></div>
<div class="money-card"><div class="label">Lunch</div><div class="val">฿300–600</div><p>Pizza, burgers, Thai mains and sharing plates. Quality is decent; you're not paying only for the view.</p></div>
<div class="money-card"><div class="label">Day bed / cabana</div><div class="val">฿1,000–2,500</div><p>Weekend, optional. A free lounger plus min spend gets you the same sun for far less.</p></div>
</div>
<p>So a relaxed couple swimming, having lunch and two drinks each lands around <strong>฿1,200–1,800 for two</strong> at most clubs — genuinely good value for a full day by a pool with sea air. Add a day bed and the party crowd and it climbs fast. For how that fits a wider budget, our <a class="inline" href="blog-pattaya-budget-7-days.html">7-day Pattaya budget guide</a> puts it in context.</p>
<h2 id="by-area">Beach clubs by area</h2>
<p>Where you base yourself decides which clubs are an easy hop. Here's the quick area read.</p>
<div class="hood">
<div class="row"><div class="area">Pratumnak Hill</div><div class="desc">The beach-club heart — Cave and Lima sit here on quiet coves between Central Pattaya and Jomtien. Real sand, sea-view pools, the best sunset scene. ฿80–120 Grab from town. See our <a class="inline" href="blog-jomtien-vs-central-pattaya.html">area comparison</a>.</div></div>
<div class="row"><div class="area">Jomtien</div><div class="desc">Calmer and more spread out — The Glass House, Rabbit Resort and Tahiti. Best for families, pool days and watersports. Walkable along Jomtien Beach Road, ฿10–30 baht-bus from the centre.</div></div>
<div class="row"><div class="area">Naklua / Wong Amat</div><div class="desc">The quiet north end with the cleanest sand. Mostly hotel beach lounges and low-key bars rather than party clubs — ideal for a slow, scenic day away from the crowds.</div></div>
<div class="row"><div class="area">Koh Larn</div><div class="desc">A 45-minute ferry from Bali Hai pier (฿30 each way). The clearest water near Pattaya, with day beds on Tawaen and Samae. A day-trip, not a quick beach-club stop.</div></div>
</div>
<h2 id="plan-your-day">How to plan your beach club day</h2>
<p>Timing is everything. Arrive <strong>before noon</strong> for the pick of free loungers, calmer water and daytime prices; the crowd, the music volume and the bills all rise toward sunset. If you want the party, target <strong>4–7pm on a weekend</strong>; if you want peace, go on a weekday morning.</p>
<p>Book a day bed ahead only at weekends or for big groups — midweek you can usually walk in. Bring cash and a card (most take both, but ATMs are a Grab away), reef-friendly sunscreen, and a cover-up if you're moving on into the evening. For ideas on filling the rest of the day, browse our <a class="inline" href="pillar-things-to-do.html">things to do in Pattaya</a> hub.</p>
<!-- FAQ -->
<h2 id="faq">Frequently asked questions</h2>
<div class="faq">
<div class="faq-item open">
<button class="faq-q" type="button">Do Pattaya beach clubs charge an entry fee? <span aria-hidden="true" class="ico">+</span></button>
<div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Most don't charge a hard ticket. Instead they set a minimum spend of about ฿300–800 per person on food and drink, which a lunch and a couple of cocktails clears easily. The exceptions are party-focused clubs like Lima at peak weekend times, and optional day beds, which run ฿1,000–2,500. You rarely pay just to walk in.</div></div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-q" type="button">Which is the best beach club in Pattaya? <span aria-hidden="true" class="ico">+</span></button>
<div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Cave Beach Club on Pratumnak Hill is the best all-rounder — real sand, a clifftop sea-view pool, a solid kitchen, sunset DJs and no hard entry fee. For families wanting a calm pool day, The Glass House on Jomtien is the better pick; for the biggest sunset party, it's Lima Beach Club, also on Pratumnak.</div></div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-q" type="button">Are Pattaya beach clubs family-friendly? <span aria-hidden="true" class="ico">+</span></button>
<div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Some are, by day. The Glass House and Rabbit Resort on Jomtien have calm pools, shade and kid-friendly food, and the family window runs until mid-afternoon. Party clubs like Lima skew 20s–30s and turn adult after dark, so go in the morning or choose Jomtien if you've brought children.</div></div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-q" type="button">How much does a day bed cost at a Pattaya beach club? <span aria-hidden="true" class="ico">+</span></button>
<div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Day beds and cabanas typically run ฿1,000–2,500 on weekends, with the party clubs at the top of that range and bottle-service tables far higher. They're optional, though — a free sun lounger plus the minimum spend gets you the same sun and pool for ฿400–600 a head, which is the better-value way to do it.</div></div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-q" type="button">Where are the best beach clubs in Pattaya located? <span aria-hidden="true" class="ico">+</span></button>
<div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">They cluster on Pratumnak Hill (Cave, Lima) and along Jomtien (The Glass House, Rabbit Resort, Tahiti), not on the busy main city beach. Pratumnak has the best sand and sunset scene, while Jomtien is calmer and more spread out. Naklua's Wong Amat offers quieter hotel beach lounges to the north.</div></div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-q" type="button">What's the best time to go to a beach club in Pattaya? <span aria-hidden="true" class="ico">+</span></button>
<div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Arrive before noon for free loungers, calmer water and daytime prices. The music, crowds and prices all climb toward sunset, so target 4–7pm on a weekend if you want the party, or a weekday morning if you want peace. November to March is the driest, most reliable season for a beach-club day.</div></div>
</div>
</div>
<p style="margin-top:var(--s5)">So: <strong>Cave for the best all-round day, The Glass House for families, Lima for the party</strong> — and the smart move at any of them is to arrive before noon, take a free lounger and skip the day bed. Pattaya's beach clubs are some of the best-value sun-and-pool days in Thailand if you play the timing right. To pair one with the right base, read our <a class="inline" href="blog-jomtien-vs-central-pattaya.html">Jomtien vs Central Go To Pattaya</a>, or start building your days on the <a class="inline" href="01-homepage-v5.html">Go To Pattaya homepage</a>.</p>
<!-- AUTHOR BIO -->
<div class="bio author">
<div class="ava">OV</div>
<div class="who">
<b>Olga Vavilova</b>
<span class="role">Senior writer · Go To Pattaya</span>
<p>Seven years living in Pattaya, writing about food, neighbourhoods and nightlife. Olga eats, drinks and walks the city she covers — no venue makes this site without a real visit. She has no commercial ties to anywhere named here. Prices and details verified June 2026.</p>
</div>
</div>
</article>
