ype": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Pattaya Beach (Central)", "description": "The famous 2.7 km city curve on Beach Road — busy, average water, but great for a stroll, sunset and a sundowner steps from food and nightlife. Best for convenience, not swimming."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Cosy Beach &amp; Sai Kaew (Pratumnak Hill)", "description": "Small, scenic, calm coves on the quiet hill between the centre and Jomtien. Cleaner water and far fewer crowds. Best for couples and a relaxed half-day."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Jomtien Beach (South)", "description": "A long, breezy 6 km of wider, calmer sand with loungers, beachfront seafood and Pattaya's water-sports hub. 5 km south. Best for a full beach day and families."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 5, "name": "Najomtien (far South)", "description": "Undeveloped, local and quiet, 10 km south toward Bang Saray. Empty sand and seafood villages, best reached by scooter. Best for escaping the crowds entirely."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 6, "name": "Koh Larn (Coral Island)", "description": "The island with genuinely clear, snorkel-worthy water — Tawaen, Samae, Tien and quiet Nual beaches. A 45-minute, ฿30 ferry from Bali Hai Pier. Best for the postcard beach day."}]}, {"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [{"@type": "Question", "name": "Which is the best beach in Pattaya?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "There's no single best — it depends on the day. For the cleanest, calmest mainland swim, Wong Amat up in Naklua wins. For a full beach day with space and water sports, Jomtien's 6 km is best. For genuinely clear, snorkel-worthy water you take the 45-minute, ฿30 ferry to Koh Larn. The central Pattaya Beach is best for a stroll and sunset, not a swim."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "What is the cleanest beach in Pattaya?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "On the mainland, Wong Amat Beach in Naklua, about 4 km north of the centre, is the cleanest and calmest — clearer water and a quieter, family crowd. Jomtien is the next best for cleanliness over its 6 km length. The central Pattaya Beach is the busiest and least clean for swimming. For genuinely clear water, take the short ferry to Koh Larn."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Is Pattaya Beach good for swimming?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Honestly, not really. Central Pattaya Beach is a busy 2.7 km city beach backed by a six-lane road, with water churned by boats and jet-skis and not always clear. It's great for a stroll, a sunset and a beer, with loungers around ฿100–150. For a proper swim, head north to Wong Amat, south to Jomtien, or take the ferry to Koh Larn."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Which beach in Pattaya is best for families?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Wong Amat in the north and Jomtien in the south are the best family beaches. Wong Amat has the calmest, cleanest water and a quiet, resort crowd; Jomtien has wider sand, more space, water sports and beachfront restaurants. Both are gentler and safer for kids than the busy central beach, and both are a cheap ฿10–20 baht-bus ride from the centre."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "How far is Jomtien Beach from Pattaya Beach?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "About 5 km, or roughly a 10-minute ride over Pratumnak Hill. The cheapest way is a Jomtien-route songthaew (baht bus) for ฿10–20, or about ฿80–150 by Grab. Because they're so close, you can easily base in one area and visit the other beaches on different days without it being a separate trip."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Where is the clearest water near Pattaya?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Not on the mainland — Pattaya sits on the Gulf coast, where the water is calmer but rarely crystal clear. For genuinely clear, turquoise, snorkel-worthy water you take the 45-minute, ฿30 public ferry from Bali Hai Pier to Koh Larn (Coral Island), where beaches like Samae, Tien and Nual have the postcard sea most visitors are picturing."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Are there quiet beaches in Pattaya?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, several. Cosy Beach and Sai Kaew on Pratumnak Hill are small, scenic and calm; Wong Amat in the north is quiet on weekday mornings; and Najomtien in the far south is undeveloped and almost empty. The central Pattaya Beach is the only truly busy one — step a few kilometres north or south and the crowds thin out fast."}}]}]$b$);
