</header>
<!-- HERO -->
<figure class="art-hero"><img alt="Beaches near pattaya 1 – The 12 bestbeaches near Pattaya, ranked" fetchpriority="high" height="506" loading="eager" src="../Pattaya-Tum-Gorseller-Resized/beaches-near-pattaya-1.webp" width="1100"/>
      <figcaption class="cap"><span class="lead"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16"><use href="#pg-pin"></use></svg> Tawaen Beach, Koh Larn · the clearest water within reach of Pattaya</span><span class="credit">Go To Pattaya</span></figcaption></figure>
<!-- TL;DR -->
<div class="tldr">
<h4><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-20"><use href="#pg-info"></use></svg> If you only have 30 seconds</h4>
<p>The <b>best beaches near Pattaya</b> are not in town. For clear water and white sand, take the <b>45-minute ferry to Koh Larn (฿30 each way)</b> and head to <b>Tawaen</b> or the quieter <b>Samae and Nual (Monkey) beaches</b>. On the mainland, <b>Jomtien</b> is the best long, swimmable city strip, <b>Wong Amat</b> in Naklua is the calmest and cleanest, and <b>Bang Saray</b> (30 minutes south) is the most local. Pattaya Beach itself ranks low for swimming but high for convenience. <b>Koh Larn beats everything for the actual sea.</b></p>
</div>
</div>
<!-- LAYOUT -->
<div class="art-layout">
<article class="art-body">
