</header>
<!-- HERO -->
<figure class="art-hero"><img alt="Beachfront areas pattaya 1 – The bestbeachfront areas in Pattayato stay" fetchpriority="high" height="506" loading="eager" src="../Pattaya-Tum-Gorseller-Resized/beachfront-areas-pattaya-1.webp" width="1100"/>
      <figcaption class="cap"><span class="lead"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-16"><use href="#pg-pin"></use></svg> Wong Amat to Jomtien · the best beachfront areas to stay in Pattaya, picked by a local</span><span class="credit">Go To Pattaya</span></figcaption></figure>
<!-- TL;DR -->
<div class="tldr">
<h4><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-20"><use href="#pg-info"></use></svg> If you only have 30 seconds</h4>
<p>For a genuinely <b>swimmable, sea-view beachfront base</b>, stay at <b>Wong Amat</b> in the quiet north (the cleanest sand in the city, mid-range rooms <b>฿1,800–4,000</b>) or on <b>Jomtien Beach</b>, a long <b>6 km</b> strip with calmer water and beachfront condos from <b>฿1,200</b>. For a small, scenic cove with sea-view rooms, <b>Pratumnak Hill</b> (Cosy Beach) is the sweet spot. <b>Beach Road in Central Pattaya</b> puts you right on the sand and steps from everything, but the city beach itself is busy and average — you trade beach quality for being walkable to nightlife. Skip beachfront entirely if your trip is about Walking Street; pick north or Jomtien if waking up to the sea is the point.</p>
</div>
</div>
