ont rooms and water sports. Beach Road wins on convenience, putting you on the sand and walkable to Walking Street, Central Festival and hundreds of restaurants. Choose Jomtien for beach days and value, Beach Road for being in the middle of the city."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Are there quiet beachfront areas in Pattaya away from the nightlife?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Wong Amat in the north is residential and resort-led with almost no bar noise, Pratumnak Hill has quiet coves like Cosy Beach, and Bang Saray, 30–40 minutes south, is an undeveloped fishing-village coast with empty sand and fresh seafood. All three keep you on the beach while staying well clear of Walking Street and the bar sois."}}]}]$b$);
