<!-- TL;DR -->
<div class="tldr">
<h4><svg aria-hidden="true" class="pg-icon is-20"><use href="#pg-info"></use></svg> If you only have 30 seconds</h4>
<p><b>Book a budget hotel</b> if you'll spend most of your day out — at the beach, on Koh Larn, eating and exploring — and just need a clean, central room to sleep. Around <b>Soi Buakhao</b> you'll pay <b>฿600–1,400 a night</b> and put the saved baht toward activities, leaving roughly <b>฿1,500–4,000 a day</b> for everything else. <b>Book beachfront</b> only if the room <em>is</em> the holiday — a balcony, a pool and a sea view you'll actually use — which in Pattaya means <b>Wong Amat, Pratumnak or Jomtien</b>, not the busy city beach, and costs <b>฿2,500–7,000+ a night</b>. For most short trips, budget central wins on value; for honeymoons, families wanting a resort, and longer stays, beachfront earns its premium.</p>
</div>
</div>
