a pool) around Soi Buakhao or Central Pattaya, from ฿600–1,400 a night. The most central, walkable base, freeing up roughly ฿20,000 over a week for activities. Best for short, active trips, tight budgets, first-timers and nightlife."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Beachfront resort", "description": "A true sea-view room with a pool and beach access in the quiet zones — Wong Amat, Pratumnak or Jomtien — from ฿2,500–7,000+ a night. Worth the premium when the room is part of the holiday. Best for honeymoons, families wanting a resort, and longer stays."}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Pool hotel near the beach", "description": "The compromise: a ฿1,200–2,500 hotel with a real pool, a few minutes back from the sand. Resort feel without beachfront prices. Best for most normal trips that aren't pure budget runs or honeymoons."}]}, {"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [{"@type": "Question", "name": "Is a beachfront hotel in Pattaya worth it?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "It depends on your trip. If the room is part of the holiday — a honeymoon, a resort week, or a family stay — a true sea-view resort in Wong Amat, Pratumnak or Jomtien (฿2,500–7,000+ a night) is genuinely worth it. But for a short, active trip where you're out all day, you'll barely use the view, and a ฿600–1,400 budget room frees up real money for activities."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Where are the best budget hotels in Pattaya?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "The best value is around Soi Buakhao and Central Pattaya, where clean, air-conditioned rooms — often with a pool — run ฿600–1,400 a night. It's also the most central area, walkable to Walking Street, the malls and hundreds of restaurants, with ฿10–20 songthaews at the door. Read recent reviews for noise and avoid the very cheapest rooms directly over a bar street."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "How much does a beachfront hotel in Pattaya cost?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "A true sea-view resort in the quiet beach zones costs roughly ฿2,500–7,000+ a night in 2026, depending on the area and season. Wong Amat and Pratumnak sit at the higher, nicer end; Jomtien is a touch cheaper and more relaxed. Off-season (May–October) you'll often find the same rooms 30–40% cheaper, which is the best beachfront value of the year."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Is Pattaya Beach good for a beachfront hotel?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Not really for the dreamy version. Pattaya Beach in Central is a busy 2.7 km city beach backed by a six-lane Beach Road, so a \"beachfront\" hotel there means a view over traffic and a working beach, not a postcard. It's great for location and nightlife, but for a real sea-view holiday, book in Wong Amat, Pratumnak or Jomtien instead."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "What's the best compromise between beachfront and budget in Pattaya?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "A ฿1,200–2,500 pool hotel a few minutes back from the beach. You get the resort feel — pool, breakfast, lift, a clean modern room — for a fraction of beachfront money, and the sand is a 5-minute walk or a ฿10 baht-bus away. It's the booking I recommend most for normal trips that aren't honeymoons or pure budget runs."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "How much can I save booking budget instead of beachfront in Pattaya?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Choosing a ฿900 budget room over a ฿4,000 beachfront one saves roughly ฿20,000 across a 7-night trip. That's enough for a Koh Larn day trip, a Nong Nooch or Sanctuary of Truth visit, a fine-dining dinner and a spa day, with change. If you'll be out most of the day anyway, that trade is usually the smarter one."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Should families book beachfront or budget in Pattaya?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Families often do better with beachfront or a good pool hotel. Direct beach access and a kids' pool save constant baht-bus trips, and a buffet breakfast simplifies mornings. Jomtien is the best-value family beachfront, while a ฿1,200–2,500 pool hotel near the beach is a cheaper option that still keeps everyone happy without the full resort price."}}]}]$b$);
